section.section:
Each board shall:
Submit to the Secretary an annual report on:
The needs of chronically ill individuals; and
The extent to which its center meets these needs;
Advise the administrative head of the center on its facilities, goals, programs, and policies;
Help in evaluating the degree to which these goals are achieved;
Review and make recommendations about the annual budget of the center;
Assume leadership in developing community understanding of the needs of chronically ill individuals; and
Carry out any other responsibility that the administrative head of the center requests.
